interest rates would achieve that goal.

00:12:08.635 --> 00:12:10.915
Common mistakes and misconceptions.

00:12:11.335 --> 00:12:14.305
Let's talk about the common
traps people fall into.

00:12:14.695 --> 00:12:17.725
Many people confuse CRR and SLR.

00:12:18.085 --> 00:12:21.775
Remember, CRR is cash kept with the RBI.

00:12:22.045 --> 00:12:26.275
While SLR is liquid assets
kept by the banks themselves,

00:12:26.635 --> 00:12:28.945
both are percentages of NDTL.

00:12:29.475 --> 00:12:33.435
Another big one is mixing up
fiscal and monetary policy.

00:12:33.825 --> 00:12:38.745
Fiscal policy is handled by the government
dealing with taxes and spending.

00:12:39.075 --> 00:12:42.855
Monetary policy is the central
bank's job, managing money,

00:12:42.855 --> 00:12:44.475
supply, and interest rates.

00:12:44.890 --> 00:12:48.160
Don't believe that commercial
banks don't create money.

00:12:48.430 --> 00:12:52.090
They absolutely do through the
process of credit creation.

00:12:52.480 --> 00:12:56.440
Also, don't misunderstand
inflation versus deflation.

00:12:56.770 --> 00:12:59.650
Inflation is a general rise in prices.

00:12:59.950 --> 00:13:02.770
Deflation is a general fall in prices.

00:13:03.160 --> 00:13:06.370
And please don't get
the rbis rolled wrong.

00:13:06.730 --> 00:13:09.820
The RBI is the regulator and supervisor.

00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:13.750
It doesn't deal directly with
the public for deposits or loans.

00:13:14.080 --> 00:13:15.700
That's for commercial banks.

00:13:16.030 --> 00:13:19.180
Lastly, don't assume
interest rates are fixed.

00:13:19.480 --> 00:13:23.470
They are dynamic and are always
changing based on central bank

00:13:23.470 --> 00:13:25.900
policies and market demand and supply.

